   Basic Educational Information
   Learn more about earthquakes.
     * Earthquakes for Kids...and Grownups
       Material for teachers and students, kids and grownups. Tutorials
       and other non-technical pages. Definitions of earthquake-related
       terms. Science fair examples. Bibliographies. (This webpage is on
       the USGS National Earthquake Hazards Program website.)
     * USGS Public Lecture Series
       Our new lecture series will teach you everything you ever wanted to
       know about earthquakes!
     * Workshops for Teachers
       Day-long workshops for teachers to learn more about earthquakes and
       hands-on activities for teaching students about earthquakes.

   Faults, Past Earthquakes & Geology
   Southern California clickable fault maps, past earthquakes in Los
   Angeles, Southern California, and California, geological photos, damage
   photos.

   Maps
   Maps of faults ,earthquakes, geology, earthquake hazards, and more.

   Publications, Products & Fact Sheets
   Non-technical information about earthquakes, faults, magnitudes, etc.
   Maps, Fact Sheets, videos and CD-ROMs. Some publications are online and
   most can be ordered. (This webpage is on the USGS National Earthquake
   Hazards Program website.)

   FAQ
   Frequently asked questions about earthquakes in California.

   Access to Southern California Earthquake Data
   Links to government agencies and non-government organizations that
   provide earthquake data. Some is available by downloading over the web.

   Earthquake FAQ

   Answers to frequently asked questions about earthquakes.


   Earthquake Image Glossary [new.gif]

   Definitions of commonly used earthquake terms.


   Earthquake ABC

   A child's view of earthquake facts and feelings.


   Putting Down Roots in Earthquake Country

   Everything you need to know as a resident of earthquake-prone Southern
   California.

